{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/http/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>In the <a href=\"./building-a-simple-registration-and-login-form-in-react\">previous section</a>, I created a simple registration form that takes user input and validates for client-side errors.</p>\n<h4>What to do next?</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>We need to send a HTTP request to the server to register a user in the database</li>\n<li>Server receives the data, and checks for any server side errors.</li>\n<li>Server tells us whether the request is accepted or rejected.</li>\n<li>Based on the server response, we need to redirect the user to the appropriate page.</li>\n</ol>\n<h6>1. Sending an HTTP request to the server</h6>\n<p>In this example, I'm going to use axios. Install <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/axios\">axios</a></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">npm i axios</code></pre></div>\n<br />\n<p>Import axios in the Registration.js</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> axios <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"axios\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<br />\n<p>Call the server onSubmit</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">handleSubmit</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token parameter\">event</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  event<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">preventDefault</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> errors <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">validate</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">setErrors</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>errors <span class=\"token operator\">||</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>errors<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">//call server</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">postData</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the <code class=\"language-text\">handleSubmit</code> method, we need to call the server right after client-side validation passes. We will place the call separately inside the <code class=\"language-text\">postData</code> method.</p>\n<br />\n<p>In the <code class=\"language-text\">postData</code> method, first call the server</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">postData</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  axios<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">post</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"http://localhost:3900/api/users\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In order to ask the server to accept data, need to send a POST request. Here, I'm sending the request to the backend server that I set up with the node.js and mogodb.</p>\n<br />\n<p>But what are we asking the server to accept? The user input.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">postData</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> userData <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> account<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    email<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> account<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>username<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    password<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> account<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>password<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  axios<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">post</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"http://localhost:3900/api/users\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> userData<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Include user input in the body of the request. The keys should match with the backend.</p>\n<br />\n<p>The request will return a promise. <a href=\"./glossary-things-i-must-know-as-a-front-end-developer\">What's a promise?</a></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">postData</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">async</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> obj <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    name<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> account<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    email<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> account<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>username<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    password<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> account<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>password<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> response <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> axios<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">post</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"http://localhost:3900/api/users\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> obj<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We need to <code class=\"language-text\">await</code> for the promise, and place the response in a const. Lastly, decorate the function with an async keyword.</p>\n<br />\n<p>Now test registering a user</p>\n<div style=\"max-width:400px; box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02); margin: 2em 0;\">\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/a17081e792d88e3aa8d423867219a203/906b5/createAccount.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 74.32432432432432%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"createAccount\" title=\"createAccount\" src=\"/static/a17081e792d88e3aa8d423867219a203/fcda8/createAccount.png\" srcset=\"/static/a17081e792d88e3aa8d423867219a203/12f09/createAccount.png 148w,\n/static/a17081e792d88e3aa8d423867219a203/e4a3f/createAccount.png 295w,\n/static/a17081e792d88e3aa8d423867219a203/fcda8/createAccount.png 590w,\n/static/a17081e792d88e3aa8d423867219a203/efc66/createAccount.png 885w,\n/static/a17081e792d88e3aa8d423867219a203/906b5/createAccount.png 950w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n</div>\n<br />\n<p>Once Register button clicked, check the Network tab in the Chrome developer tool</p>\n<div style=\"max-width:400px; box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02); margin: 2em 0;\">\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/468d36e07f5fd76dbf4ee749b6d5ae99/f32b7/post_network.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 64.1891891891892%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"post network\" title=\"post network\" src=\"/static/468d36e07f5fd76dbf4ee749b6d5ae99/fcda8/post_network.png\" srcset=\"/static/468d36e07f5fd76dbf4ee749b6d5ae99/12f09/post_network.png 148w,\n/static/468d36e07f5fd76dbf4ee749b6d5ae99/e4a3f/post_network.png 295w,\n/static/468d36e07f5fd76dbf4ee749b6d5ae99/fcda8/post_network.png 590w,\n/static/468d36e07f5fd76dbf4ee749b6d5ae99/efc66/post_network.png 885w,\n/static/468d36e07f5fd76dbf4ee749b6d5ae99/f32b7/post_network.png 1136w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n</div>\nUnder users, Status code shows 200 OK. Successfully saved the user data in the server.\n<br />\n<p>It successfully shows up in the MongoDB as well</p>\n<div style=\"max-width:400px; box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.02); margin: 2em 0;\">\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/0b4dab47a5bf632135cfca99a7342238/36eca/userMongo.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 16.89189189189189%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAAAfklEQVQI12WOWwrDMAwEc/9jpn8x9GE7lq2Ht5Lbj5IKBsQILbuJKtQMVDLsLJhnBuoTMyhOczfnH2aB/TChnrWZH8cYuO070j0jPSpKbejUIe6VGaIG/rJ2sRV6nQjeop2I4EgHaiMUErwao3ZZECtoiPtwjNY/e/zh0jrcG6Wj61U2TIDLAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"userMongo\" title=\"userMongo\" src=\"/static/0b4dab47a5bf632135cfca99a7342238/fcda8/userMongo.png\" srcset=\"/static/0b4dab47a5bf632135cfca99a7342238/12f09/userMongo.png 148w,\n/static/0b4dab47a5bf632135cfca99a7342238/e4a3f/userMongo.png 295w,\n/static/0b4dab47a5bf632135cfca99a7342238/fcda8/userMongo.png 590w,\n/static/0b4dab47a5bf632135cfca99a7342238/efc66/userMongo.png 885w,\n/static/0b4dab47a5bf632135cfca99a7342238/c83ae/userMongo.png 1180w,\n/static/0b4dab47a5bf632135cfca99a7342238/36eca/userMongo.png 1526w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n</div>\n<p>To be continued...</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Basic HTTP authentication","date":"08.07.2020"},"excerpt":"In the previous section, I created a simple registration form that takes user input and validates for client-side errors. What to do next…"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/http/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3159585216","63159454"]}